description: For sale: $319,900. This Highly desirable 3rd floor, East facing condo overlooking the pond is just what you are looking for. The spacious living room has a gas fireplace and opens up to the generous deck and additional storage room where the home's mechanicals are located. The generous master bedroom has an en suite bath with large walk-in closet. The den is perfect as a home office. 9 foot ceilings and in unit laundry are two other features of this home. Overnight guests will enjoy the community's guest suites. As a homeowner, you also have access to a private storage room, a community room, exercise room, and workshop. Close to shopping, dining, and entertainment, you will love this move-in ready condo. Welcome Home!

Highlights include a spacious foyer that leads to the grand living room with arched windows and 10' ceilings, a center-island kitchen with both informal and formal dining areas and a large master suite featuring an ensuite master bath with a jetted tub, separate shower and a large walk-in closet. The walkout lower level has a 22x16 family room with a wood-burning fplc, two large BR's (one with a walk-in closet) and a ceramic tiled full bath. Plus, there's a large 27x10 utility/laundry room and a 14x11 storage room with built-in shelving. In addition, there's an over-sized 19x22 finished garage, a 7x6 main floor mudroom that could accommodate a second washer/dryer (if desired) and a new cedar shake roof in 2013! All ideally located on a culdesac with just 28 homes and across the street from Bredesen Park!

description: For sale: $2,145,000. A one owner custom built home, maintained to perfection, pet free and meticulously cared for. The best of both worlds, nestled on nearly 1 acre of meticulously cared for grounds viewing a peaceful pond yet conveniently located to amazing schools, shopping, dining and parks. This home boasts an open spacious floor plan with formal dining with butler's pantry, 2-story great room, private office, large gourmet kitchen. Spacious mud room w/walk-in sports gear closet. Upper level master suite showcases an exquisite master bath, two additional large ensuite bedrooms and the convenient laundry room. Walkout lower level features a large family room, exercise room, wet bar, bed and bath. Edina school system, Open enrollment policy 510 provides priority placement for Edina residents.

The lower level amusement room with its gas fireplace would be fantastic for movie nights or overflow guest space. There is also a convenient 3/4 bath on this level/attached over-sized two+ car garage and a concrete driveway. This is a great location and opportunity. Relocation documents are required.

For sale: $1,760,000. A beautifully crafted home, exemplifying impeccable architecture, design and attention to detail. description: Recently sold: $567,000. Charming home on a corner lot in a quiet neighborhood! Two bedrooms on main, two bedrooms on lower walk-out level, plus a variety of gathering spaces. Exterior highlights include deck, lower patio and spacious fenced-in backyard.

Recently sold: $575,000. Excellent location, incredible condition!  Updated 4 bedroom, 3 bath rambler on a quiet, private cul-de-sac in the high-demand Countryside neighborhood. An open floor plan makes entertaining easy with several gathering spaces.  The updated kitchen features stately custom cabinets, granite counter tops, newer stainless steel appliances, a unique breakfast bar, and hardwood floors. If you are looking for a well appointed and updated condo with unsurpassed amenities, look no further! The roomy lower level entertainment area is filled with light and includes a guest suite with 3/4 bathroom. Todd Park is right down the hill and has great green space in the summer and an incredible hockey rink in the winter. Come see this amazing home!

Recently sold: $365,000. This fabulous space is truly a one of a kind opportunity.  This is a non-mls opportunity as the current owner is transitioning into assisted living care. description:
Recently sold: $1,075,000. Stunning and unique wooded lot in one of Edina's most desired areas. Situated on more than 2/3 of an acre in the Highlands neighborhood, the back yard adjoins Highlands Park and is just steps from the Interlachen Country Club.  The home enjoys serene views of over 40 acres of parkland and natural areas with quiet wooded walking trails for communing with wildlife and waterfowl; regular visitors include great herons, bald eagles, double breasted cormorants, great egrets and many species of ducks and geese, along with turtles, frogs and toads.

This home in the Edina School District enjoys the convenience of first ring suburb living while accessing the serenity of the Northwoods in its back yard.  In addition to a peaceful screened structure near the water, this gorgeous lot has a tastefully remodeled 50?s rambler with five bedrooms and over 4500 square feet of living space.  An expansive modern kitchen sits at the center of the open floor plan.  This exceptional lot is filled with dozens of towering mature trees.  Norway spruce and red pine, bur oak, eastern white pine and blue spruce provide privacy, shade and habitat for many varieties of songbirds, raptors and owls.  A great setting for a distinctive home in Edina.
Recently sold: $738,500.

Recently sold: $510,000. This home is located on a quest street w/large windows filling the home w/natural light. The sun porch overlooks a large backyard lined with large trees. Hardwood floors, 3/4 master bath, lower level family room,  2 fireplaces, formal living and dining room. Over 2300 F.S.F.

Recently sold: $645,000. Step into this authentic Cape Cod 3 bed, 4 bath and be amazed with the attention to detail! Such a great floor plan with a main floor master suite, formal living and dining rooms, den, eat-in kitchen (with fireplace!) and family room. Generous storage rooms in the walk out lower level as well as nicely finished spaces. Attached garage. A happy gardener lived here and her yard is a testament to her long hours and keen eye. Flowers bloom all summer long....you will love the birds and butterflies that are drawn to this magical place. Edina public schools newly passed 510c changes open enrollment policy, now offering priority placement for Edina residents.

description: Recently sold: $1,030,000. Grand living spaces and a gourmet kitchen set the stage for fabulous entertaining and living! description:
Recently sold: $3,075,000. Once a lifetime, a gathering of artisans, craftsmen, new, and old world elements tasked with creating a residence, unmatched in beauty and livability. 
The setting starts with a gated, covered arch carriage house approach ( an artifact from the Whittman Family Farm, now collector space for a regal fleet), and winds thru towering conifers and majestic hardwoods to this landmark home. 
Private, water reflected golf course views, charming cobbled walkways and drive, and a captivating masterpiece of Bavarian influence and grand sense of arrival. 
Slate, stone, copper, and full timbered accents greet one to an imposing, steepled turret, a grand reception hall, rich woodwork details, and anchored by a "floating" 3 story, winding stone stairwell ( one of our era's most important architectural achievements). There is an opulent main level master suite with one of 6 new baths, elegant, voluminous public rooms, family rooms, theater, as well as venues for billiards and wine cellar entertaining. 
Both kitchens are new, tastefully appointed with the appropriate level of finish and fine accoutrements. 
Incidentals include, finely crafted floors and millwork, impeccably maintained and engineered mechanicals, terraces, dock, and beautiful gardens. 
Oh, and the two very special rooms, including the turret top "sanctuary" and the richly detailed library of old growth, book matched hardwood and adjacent pub.

The interior features: all-new, gourmet kitchen with giant center island, quartzite countertops, and stainless steel appliances; dreamy master bedroom with his and hers walk-in closets and a private spa like bathroom; matte finish maple hardwoods and new carpet; grand dining room; 9+ foot ceilings; custom millwork; main floor laundry; Anderson Windows; vaulted ceilings and custom lighting; built-ins; wet bar; sauna; exercise room; specialty sound system wired throughout; 2 fireplaces; heated garage; and so much more. You'll find something special around every corner. The lower level walks out to a stone patio and maintenance free yard.

Recently sold: $243,000. Welcome to Edina West Condominiums - Large 1,758sf Corner Unit - This 2.5 Bedroom - 1 3/4 Bath - 1 Large Screened Porch - 3 Porches total - Bright Open Flow - Wonderful Gas Fireplace - Overwhelming Storage space. Den could be converted into a 3rd bedroom if wish.  Great open floorpan with space needed if downsizing.  Daily sunshine from any one of the 3 porches - Work out in the wonderful Recreation Center, indoor & outdoor pools & tennis courts - Enjoy pickle ball or become active if you wish with the gardening team or good neighbors group and more.  Very quiet on the decibel scale....with windows closed, lower than 20 and on porch with wet roads around 45 or so.  Highway decibel levels are up around 80 or so. Relax and Enjoy all that Edina West has to offer.  Have a great day ahead!

description:
Recently sold: $727,500. **Open House for Saturday 6/15 has been cancelled**
Sunlit 2 story home in the heart of the Countryside neighborhood and steps from Bredesen Park & Countryside Park.  Your family will appreciate this .32 acre lot featuring gorgeous landscaping by Bachmans, a large deck for you to relax & a flat backyard to play ball or have your pets run- there is an electric fence for your furry family members. This home features a nice mix of classic & rustic touches including: alder cabinetry, gorgeous granite countertops in the eat-in kitchen, barnwood door on main floor powder room & vaulted 3 season porch with wood plank ceiling. 1st floor offers a main floor bedroom (currently used as an office), spacious living and dining areas with gorgeous hardwood floors, a family room with a cozy gas fireplace, a convenient main-floor laundry with spacious mudroom. The upper level features 4 bedrooms on one level, private 3/4 master bath & an updated full bath with marble countertop. Watch a movie in the finished lower level 2nd family room & game room.

description: Recently sold: $705,000. Beautiful, newly updated 5bd/4bth 2 story home on large spacious lot. Quiet street, family friendly neighborhood, Edina schools, walking distance to Walnut Ridge Park & Bredesen Park. Beautiful custom kitchen w/ Sub Zero appliances & granite countertops. New paint - interior/exterior. Refinished hardwood floors & new carpet throughout house. Newer Marvin Windows, Hardie siding, garage doors, roof, furnace & ac. Lrg grand sized MBR-Vanity walk in Closet w/ window. Oversized 3 car garage.

Recently sold: $540,000. Absolutely stunning remodel in a prime Edina location.  This home has been completely renovated with 3 bedrooms on one level, 2 1/2 baths, 2,254 finished square feet and a 2-car attached garage.  Gorgeous new kitchen with enameled cabinets, pantry, granite counter tops and stainless steel appliances.   Very open main floor complete with gleaming wood floors and screened porch.  Lower level features a huge family room, bath and walks out to a private flat backyard. This home has it all!

Recently sold: $627,500. Impeccably maintained Edina home located on a quiet Cul-De-Sac just steps from Highlands Elementary School and Playground. Sunlight filled, airy, open floor plan that is fabulous for entertaining!  Dramatic living room with whitewashed wood vaulted statement ceiling and an attractive fireplace.
Main floor living room, dining room and family room flow into the
updated chefs kitchen with all stainless steel appliances including a double oven and a 5 burner gas stove.  There is loads of storage to house all of your cooking gadgets and appliances. 
The main floor office has two large skylights providing wonderful natural lighting.  Just off of the heated three car garage is a conveniently located laundry/mudroom and powder-room.
The upper level contains 3 bedrooms - a large master bedroom with an en suite 3/4 bath and two big closets.  There are also two additional bedrooms with lots of windows and huge closets and a cedar closet.  These bedrooms share a full bath with double sinks.
The lower level boasts a large carpeted entertainment room with a fireplace, an exercise room, homework desk/cubby, and another bedroom and bath perfect for your teen or to use as a nanny's quarters.
The lower level also contains two large storage rooms with built-in shelving.
Your party can flow out into the 3 season porch which is connected to a large deck system adjacent to a spectacular greenhouse that is perfect for gardening all year round.
Fenced in back yard, a large raspberry patch and many perennials can be found throughout the property.
Recently sold: $530,000.

description:
Recently sold: $1,073,400. Have you been looking at new construction homes in Edina or Southwest Minneapolis and just have not found the right fit for your lifestyle and your budget?
If so, building a new custom home designed just for you may be a great option.  
MJL Homes has over 25 years of building experience and over 800 homes built.  We are a small boutique builder that specializes in building homes in Edina, Linden Hills, Fulton, St. Louis Park, Golden Valley, Minnetonka and Bloomington.
Our ideal client is looking to build a new construction home between $850,000 and $1,000,000.
We have several amazing floor plans that work in Edina, Linden Hills and Fulton for under $925,000.
Please come and see the quality fit and finish of an MJL Home by visiting us at our Model Home at 5705 Bernard Place.  Come and see the quality fit & finish of an MJL Home.  We have open house every weekend if you would like to learn more. We want to answer your building questions.  We are here to help.
The main floor of this home has a large great room with gas fireplace and custom built-ins, office, gourmet kitchen and formal dining room with coffer-ed ceiling.This home is specifically designed for entertaining. Large windows across the back of the home let in tons of natural light.
The spacious gourmet kitchen has white custom cabinetry with granite counter tops and a quartz island, high efficiency stainless steel appliances, including a 36 inch gas cook top, hardwood floors and a large pantry and mud room, with drop zone and charging station. Tons of storage!
Enjoy a very large owner's retreat with luxurious master bath, heated floors, a separate tub & shower and large walk in closet. 3 additional large Bedrooms on the upper level. There is also a Jr Suite located on the upper level. Laundry room is conveniently located on the upper level as well. 
The finished Lower Level has 9 ft ceilings and includes a huge 39 x 17 family room with a gas fireplace, wet bar and game area for family fun. There is a 5th bedroom and 3/4 bath in the lower level too. 
This home has a very large backyard with a sprinkler system. Perfect for summer grilling and entertaining. 
Our goal: Custom Designs. . . . .Stunning Results.

description: Recently sold: $258,000. Remodeled corner unit with 3 patios, one fully screened, overlooking a private park-like setting. It has one of the nicest kitchens in all of Edina West. First-floor access through patios allows easy access to association grounds with picnic tables, grills and paver patio. The nearby trails, fountains, outdoor pool and tennis courts truly make Edina West one opf the most sought-after condo communities. Add an indoor pool, whirlpool, tennis and pickle ball court, exercise room, sauna, locker room, raquet ball court, pool table, several party rooms and an underground heated garage and car washing station, you have a winning combination!

Recently sold: $835,000. Every room in this walkout rambler has been completely updated! New roof, new Marvin windows, vaulted ceiling, Wolf range, two fireplaces, master suite. Open floor plan with great flow and function. Beautiful custom design details including reclaimed wood beams and pillars, wainscoting, built-ins, tongue-in-groove and beadboard accents. Refinished hardwood floors. 2-car tuck-under garage. Generous fenced backyard with privacy and room for a pool. Lower level includes a second kitchen and secluded bedroom, perfect for nanny?s quarters or mother-in-law suite.

Recently sold: $1,229,000. This beautiful single-story home boasts a flowing and spacious floor plan with gorgeous updates highlighted by sun-filled rooms. Find 4 bedrooms on the main level with the master suite tucked away on opposite side of the living space for both privacy and peace of mind. The suite offers a walk-in shower with steamer and walk-in closets. The kitchen is rich and warm with a massive island for eating and cooking and opens up to family room and massive windows. The lower level offers endless room for entertaining and play with a wet bar, rec room and additional family room! Walk-out to a lush backyard and beautiful stone patio!

description: Recently sold: $368,500. Meticulously maintained rambler on landscaped corner lot, steps to Birchcrest Park, and a short walk from Countryside Park and School. Superb mid-century features combined with thoughtful updates. Light-filled living room with stone wood-burning fireplace, formal dining room, and access to remodeled 3 season porch. Renovated eat-in kitchen with informal dining area and adjacent den/tv room (converted from bedroom). description:
Recently sold: $750,000. For more information or to schedule a private showing, please contact Eric and Sharla Stafford at 952-470-2575. Perfectly located on a quiet, tree-lined street, this custom home offers main-level living at its finest! Beautifully refreshed inside and out, features warm and welcoming spaces that you are sure to enjoy.  
 
Hardwood floors lead you from the Foyer into the Great Room where you will find 11? foot ceilings and an inviting gas fireplace flanked by custom built-ins that hide your TV and components. Adjacent to the Great Room is a Gourmet Kitchen which features cherry cabinetry with quiet-close and pull-out drawers, granite countertops and a stainless-steel appliance package. The large island offers an elevated breakfast bar where guests can visit while you cook delicious meals to share. Complete with a Dining Room, this open floor plan will become a favorite gathering space for every celebration and family get-together.
 
Just off the Dining Room, you'll find the Four-Season Porch. Walls of windows fill the space with natural light and a patio door leads out to the Deck. Curl up with a good book or sit back with your morning coffee while enjoying this tranquil space.
 
Nestled behind the Great Room is the private Master Suite. The room features luxurious details from the tray ceiling with crown molding to the beautiful chandelier. The sellers added plantation shutters to the picture windows that overlook the backyard allowing light into the room while providing you with privacy. A master bathroom offers spa finishes with separate His and Her vanities featuring marble countertops, a large soaking tub and a tiled walk-in shower. 

A quiet Home Office, updated Powder Room with furniture style vanity, and a Laundry & Mud Room complete the main level. 
 
Fully finished, the walkout lower level was designed for pure entertainment. With a cozy gas fireplace, the Family Room is ideal for movie night while an adjacent Game Room offers plenty of space for a billiard table. With radiant in-floor heating and 9' ceilings the lower level is as comfortable as the main level all year long. Three Guest Bedrooms and a full Bathroom complete the lower level. If you'd like, you can use one of the bedrooms as an Exercise or Craft Room.
 
If you enjoy spending time outdoors, the private Deck and Patio are sure to please. The sellers have added mature trees and additional landscaping around the backyard creating a private setting where you can dine al fresco or relax in peace.   
 
The Abbey at Chapel Hill provides its residents with maintenance-free living. Lawn care, snow removal and garbage service are all managed by the association. Adding to the convenience, this home is perfectly located close to shopping, dining, parks and schools. You will enjoy easy access to all that Edina and the Twin Cities has to offer. Welcome Home.

description:
Recently sold: $459,000. This Edina single family home is available for a Mid July or Aug 1st move in. Please note that the owners do plan on building a new home on this site in 2-3 years and the property will be rented as is. Overall the property is in good shape, there are some small things missing such as trim and vents. If you do wish to paint while you live here you are welcome to do that with approval.

The pictures were just taken so what you see is what you will get. Be confident while living here we will service the property as needed in case their plans do change. If you do have questions or concerns please contact me anytime.

Walking into the home you will find a spacious living room with fireplace. Through the living room you have a dining area and sitting room. The kitchen has another table area and the main level has laundry in the back. 

The main floor has two bedrooms and a full bath.

Upstairs you will find two more bedrooms which are both smaller in size as well as a 3/4th bath. 

Outside you have a very large 3 car garage.

While living here you will be responsible for Lawn+Snow and all Utilities including w/s/w, gas, and electric.

Pets are welcome with positive rental reference and credit score. (Dog deposit $500, Cat $200)

Applications will be available at time of showing or online. Each application is $50 per adult and can be paid with a credit or debit card. Application is based off income, credit, rental/work history and includes a criminal background check.

Any questions please call or email Billy.

Broker: GUARDIAN PROPERTY MANAGEMENT AND SERVICES LLC
Agent: Billy Sommers

Rental Terms: Rent: $2,195, Application Fee: $50, Security Deposit: $2,195, Available 7/13/18

Pet Policy: Cats allowed, Dogs allowed This property allows self guided viewing without an appointment. Contact for details.

description:
Recently sold: $299,900. 5808 Schaefer Rd

                 **Available June 1st**
                  (possibly mid-May)

Open to starting the lease at a later date. We live 2 doors down, so finding great neighbors is the highest of priorities.

Remodeled less than a year ago, from top to bottom. Sits across from Bredesen Park.

The property consists of 3 bedrooms (2 upstairs), 2 baths (1 up, 1 down), laid out over 2540 SQ FT. It has 2 natural fireplaces (1 up, 1 down), and a washer and dryer downstairs (laundry chute in master). A spacious backyard, with a huge deck, and a very large attached 2-car garage round out the property. 

Original hardwood floors encompass almost the entirety of the upstairs, including the large family room (reclaimed fireplace mantel), and adjacent dining room. Aside from the 2 bedrooms upstairs, there's a 200 SQ FT sundeck overlooking the yard. Lots of closet space in both bedrooms, with 2 closets and a built-in dresser/cabinet residing in the master bedroom alone. 

The kitchen includes brand new light fixtures, stainless steel appliances, backsplash, etc.

The downstairs consists largely of brand new flooring, a large living room, a natural fireplace, a bathroom, a 200 SQ FT laundry/mud room/whatever-floats-your-boat room;  with multiple access doors to the garage and back yard, and multiple closets throughout.

The following items are brand new via the remodel:

*All of the appliances in the kitchen 
* Water heater
* Washer and dryer 
* Furnace 
* AC unit 
* 16 x 10 deck 
* Flooring downstairs 
* Light fixtures throughout  
* Water Softener

And a whole lot more!

Lawn maintenance, snow removal, garbage/recycling, and water are included in your rent.

The property sits just across from Bredesen Park, and within Edina's school district. 

We are dog and cat friendly. We live a few doors down, and I'm a stay-at-home dad, so I can accommodate a wide range of showing times, as long as it is in accordance with the current tenants. Just give me a call: 312-401-6407 Mark.

Thank you!
